**Why Parameterized Queries Work**

Parameterized queries work by separating the SQL code from the input data. Instead of concatenating the input data into the SQL code, you pass it as a separate parameter to the query. The SQL library then takes care of properly escaping the input data, ensuring that it is treated as a parameter and not as part of the SQL code.

This approach prevents attackers from injecting malicious SQL code by providing specially crafted input data. Even if an attacker provides input data that looks like SQL code, it will be treated as a parameter and will not be executed as SQL.

For example, consider the following vulnerable code:

```javascript
const query = "SELECT * FROM products WHERE name = '" + userInput + "'";
```

If an attacker provides the following input:

```sql
