```

The resulting SQL query would be:

```sql
SELECT * FROM products WHERE name = '' OR 1=1 --'
```

This query would return all products, because the `OR 1=1` condition is always true.

In contrast, a parameterized query would treat the input data as a parameter and would not be vulnerable to this type of attack:

```javascript
const query = "SELECT * FROM products WHERE name = ?";
db.query(query, [userInput], (err, results) => {
  // ...
});
```

In this case, the input data would be properly escaped and would not be executed as SQL.

